body:
@mgwidmann Thank you for your report.

The `options` argument is ignored because the [`Warden::SessionSerializer#store`](https://github.com/hassox/warden/blob/906edf86c6c31be917a921097031b89361d022e8/lib/warden/session_serializer.rb#L22) doest no accept this argument.

In the Devise `bypass` option [documentation](https://github.com/plataformatec/devise/blob/7df57d5081f9884849ca15e4fde179ef164a575f/lib/devise/controllers/sign_in_out.rb#L18) says it will "bypass warden callbacks and stores the user straight in session". When you use `bypass` you want to store in the session, and it has more precedence than `store: false`.
